Abu Dhabi Commercial, Aramex, Emirates NBD: Gulf Equity Preview

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-04-27T02:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-27/abu-dhabi-commercial-aramex-emirates-nbd-gulf-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in Persian Gulf markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and prices are from the last close.  Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  retreated 0.2 percent to
1,634.75, the lowest level since April 14. Abu Dhabi’s  ADX
General Index (ADSMI)  slipped less than 0.1 percent.        Abu Dhabi Commercial Bank PJSC (ADCB)  : The United Arab
Emirates’ third-biggest bank said first-quarter profit more than
doubled to 574.4 million dirhams ($156 million) from 218.6
million dirhams a year earlier. The shares decreased 0.4 percent
to 2.69 dirhams when they last traded April 25.        Abu Dhabi Islamic Bank (ADIB)  : The United Arab Emirates’
second-biggest bank complying with Shariah
rules expects the market to be "challenging" this year after
posting a 3 percent rise in first-quarter profit. The shares
fell 0.3 percent to 3.21 dirhams.       Aramex PJSC (ARMX UH): The Middle East’s largest courier
company said first-quarter profit increased 5 percent to 49.8
million dirhams helped by growth in Gulf markets and
acquisitions. The shares declined 2.1 percent to 1.87 dirhams.  Emirates NBD PJSC (EMIRATES)  : The U.A.E.’s biggest bank
by assets is "comfortable" with repaying maturing debt, Chief
Financial Officer Surya Subramanian said. The bank is targeting
4 percent growth in loans this year, Chief Executive Officer
 Rick Pudner  said. The shares advanced 2.4 percent to 3.85
dirhams.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  